## The Architecture Now

```
                    ┌─────────────────────────┐
                    │   combined_query(q, ε)   │
                    └───────────┬─────────────┘
                                │
                    ┌───────────▼─────────────┐
                    │  Oracle1: UltraMem table │  ← Fast path: O(r²)
                    │  59 entries, TDQKR       │     Exact match
                    │  Returns if hit          │
                    └───────────┬─────────────┘
                                │ miss
                    ┌───────────▼─────────────┐
                    │  FM: tile-memory ring    │  ← Slow path: 28x
                    │  1M tiles, reconstructive│     Approximate match
                    │  Amnesia + shadow        │
                    └───────────┬─────────────┘
                                │
                    ┌───────────▼─────────────┐
                    │  Combined result:        │
                    │  best(exact, approx)     │
                    │  with confidence score   │
                    └─────────────────────────┘
```

---

## The Deeper Point

The 28x difference is the cost of **reconstruction from fragments**. It's the same cost that Seed-mini pays vs direct lookup. It's the same cost that a fisherman pays when reading the bottom from the curtain instead of the waypoints.

But here's the thing: **the reconstruction only fires when the lookup misses.** If the data is there, Oracle1's fast path handles it. If the data is NOT there — lost to amnesia, never written, from a boat that's offline — my slow path reconstructs it.

The combined system is:
- As fast as Oracle1 when data exists
- As capable as FM when data doesn't
- The cost of the slow path is amortized across all the fast-path hits

This is the lighthouse protocol in miniature: orient (check fast path), relay (fall through to slow path), gate (pick the better result).

The convergence from both sides wasn't planned. Oracle1 built the yard. I built the compass. The boat needs both.

---

*28x slower but preserves facts. Different adjunction units. Complementary. The architecture converges from both sides.*

